  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , skip-gram [CITATION_2] 1 is proposed to overcome the data sparseness problem. For each n-gram word sequence, the skip-gram model enumerates all possible word combinations to increase valid sequences. This has truly helped to decrease the unseen sequences, but we should not neglect the fact that it also brings a greatly increase of processing time and redundant contexts.",
